\AUDbegin 247.6470
\AUDend 249.7451
\wav SOUNDFILE 247.6470 249.7451

\rf Olr.Anguille.33
\tv Rakraqa mō gis gat, nēy van, nēy wō m̄am̄arat nēy mō gis wēt, nēy van.
\tf Les femmes se saisirent de leurs paniers, les hommes de leurs perches; et ils se mirent tous en chemin.
\ta The women seized their baskets, the men their carrying poles, and off they all went.
\AUDbegin 249.7451
\AUDend 253.1149
\wav SOUNDFILE 249.7451 253.1149
\pc *
\pc *  *

\rf Olr.Anguille.34
\tv Nēy van van van van van, lē tina mataalē, m̄ay mere ni m-ron̄ vēlēē, ron̄ nēy mō ras nok.
\tf Alors qu'ils se trouvaient encore en chemin, l'Anguille qui écoutait attentivement comprit qu'ils s'étaient éloignés.
\ta They all walked away, one after the other. While they were still somewhere along the road, the Eel had understood that they were already a long way away.
\AUDbegin 253.1149
\AUDend 258.8372
\wav SOUNDFILE 253.1149 258.8372

\rf Olr.Anguille.35
\tv Nōrō putputē ne tē pipira ti nōtam, ron̄ “Kumuy ga ēlwoy tutujun̄ lē gēmēl, a! Kumuy mētē vanvan ley ras jēn! Kumuy ēlwoy tok mētē rakat.”
